==English==
===Noun===
'''windup'''
# the act of [[ending]] or [[concluding]] something
# the last part of something; a [[conclusion]]
#(''British'') A [[practical joke]] or [[tease]]
===Adjective===
'''windup'''
# operated by a [[coiled]] [[spring]] that is [[wound]] by [[hand]]
===Transitive verb===
'''to windup'''
#(''British'') To [[convince]] somebody that something is [[true]], especially when it is not, often for [[humorous]] purposes
#:''George Bush says that God told him to invade Iraq! Are you '''winding me up'''?''
===Alternative spellings===
*[[wind-up]]
